⚙️ System Architecture (Make It Real)

1. Roles

👤 Data Farmers (anyone)
	•	complete quests
	•	collect/label/verify data
	•	earn rewards

🧭 Guilds
	•	groups that specialize (e.g., urban mapping, language, biology, retail trends)
	•	create custom quests
	•	build reputation

🏗️ Orchestrator (platform layer)
	•	distributes tasks
	•	verifies quality
	•	routes data to buyers (AI labs, companies, research orgs)

⸻

2. Quest Types (This is the gold)

🌍 Physical World Capture
	•	“Film how people navigate this store layout”
	•	“Capture traffic patterns at X time”
	•	“Scan and label local plant species”

🧠 Cognitive / Interpretation Tasks
	•	annotate emotions in conversations
	•	describe cultural nuances
	•	explain “why” something feels right/wrong

🗣️ Language + Culture Layer (your translator idea)
	•	translate slang with context
	•	explain cultural meaning behind phrases
	•	record local dialects and speech patterns

This is huge because:

AI struggles most with context, culture, and nuance

⸻

🎮 Gamification Layer (Critical)

You must make this feel like:
	•	exploration
	•	contribution
	•	progression

Not:
	•	boring microtasks

Mechanics:
	•	levels, ranks, unlocks
	•	rare quests
	•	guild competitions
	•	“legendary discoveries”
	•	streaks and mastery paths

But careful:

If you over-optimize for fun, you destroy data quality
If you over-optimize for efficiency, you lose participation

Balance = key invariant

