⚠️ Second-Order Effects (Where This Breaks)

1. 📉 Data Quality Collapse

People will:
	•	fake submissions
	•	game rewards
	•	spam low-effort data

Fix:
	•	multi-layer validation (peer + AI + reputation)
	•	delayed payouts for verification
	•	stake/slash systems (bad data = penalty)

⸻

2. 🧍 Exploitation Risk

Turns into:
	•	digital sweatshop
	•	underpaid labor
	•	invisible work extraction

Fix:
	•	transparent pricing per task
	•	minimum payout floors
	•	ownership/royalty models for high-value data

⸻

3. 🕵️ Privacy Nightmare

You’re literally asking people to record reality.

Fix (non-negotiable):
	•	strict consent rules
	•	automatic anonymization
	•	“no-go zones” (private spaces, sensitive contexts)
	•	on-device filtering before upload

⸻

4. 🌍 Cultural Flattening (Ironically)

If done wrong:
	•	dominant cultures overwrite smaller ones
	•	everything gets normalized

This is where your translator insight matters:

AI should translate without collapsing difference

